Others: Joel Embiid made his season debut against the New York Knicks after missing the first nine games due to a left knee injury and a three-game suspension.
Embiid struggled in his return, scoring 13 points on 2-for-11 shooting from the field, 8-for-8 from the free throw line, 3 rebounds, 5 assists, and 1 block in 26 minutes.
Embiid's team, the Philadelphia 76ers, lost to the Knicks 111-99.
Karl-Anthony Towns, a native of central New Jersey, had one of his best performances as a Knick with 21 points, 13 rebounds, and 6 assists.
The Knicks don't have the injury issues that the 76ers are facing, with their starting lineup and sixth man Deuce McBride available for all 10 games.
